description: Searches routing profiles in an Amazon Connect instance, with optional filtering.

parameters.name: InstanceId
parameters.description: The identifier of the Amazon Connect instance. You can find the instance ID in the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the instance.

parameters.name: SearchFilter
parameters.description: Filters to be applied to search results. TagFilter (dict) --- An object that can be used to specify Tag conditions inside the SearchFilter. This accepts an OR of AND (List of List) input where: Top level list specifies conditions that need to be applied with OR operator Inner list specifies conditions that need to be applied with AND operator. OrConditions (list) --- A list of conditions which would be applied together with an OR condition. (list) --- (dict) --- A leaf node condition which can be used to specify a tag condition, for example, HAVE BPO = 123. TagKey (string) --- The tag key in the tag condition. TagValue (string) --- The tag value in the tag condition. AndConditions (list) --- A list of conditions which would be applied together with an AND condition. (dict) --- A leaf node condition which can be used to specify a tag condition, for example, HAVE BPO = 123. TagCondition (dict) --- A leaf node condition which can be used to specify a tag condition. TagValue (string) --- The tag value in the tag condition.

nested_items.name: RoutingProfiles
nested_items.description: Information about the routing profiles.

nested_items.name: InstanceId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the Amazon Connect instance. You can find the instance ID in the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the instance.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the routing profile.

nested_items.name: RoutingProfileArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the routing profile.

nested_items.name: RoutingProfileId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the routing profile.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: The description of the routing profile.

nested_items.name: MediaConcurrencies
nested_items.description: The channels agents can handle in the Contact Control Panel (CCP) for this routing profile.

nested_items.name: Channel
nested_items.description: The channels that agents can handle in the Contact Control Panel (CCP).

nested_items.name: Concurrency
nested_items.description: The number of contacts an agent can have on a channel simultaneously.

nested_items.name: CrossChannelBehavior
nested_items.description: Defines the cross-channel routing behavior for each channel that is enabled for this Routing Profile. For example, this allows you to offer an agent a different contact from another channel when they are currently working with a contact from a Voice channel.

nested_items.name: BehaviorType
nested_items.description: Specifies the other channels that can be routed to an agent handling their current channel.

nested_items.name: DefaultOutboundQueueId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the default outbound queue for this routing profile.

nested_items.name: AgentAvailabilityTimer
nested_items.description: Whether agents with this routing profile will have their routing order calculated based on time since their last inbound contact or longest idle time.
